user.name: biologist
text: Finally reached base camp. Time to get busy. In training they said it can be months before we're done. Bring it.

user.name: biologist
text: Fourth day at base camp, there's a tower that isn't on the map. Well, --> I think it's a tower.

user.name: biologist
text: The surveyor says it's impossible, it's not here. We're all hallucinating then…

user.name: biologist
text: Staying occupied. This place is a protected wildlife refuge. An ecosystem made of many wonders.

user.name: biologist
text: Hard to remind myself to be the scientist, not the hiker.

user.name: biologist
text: No one else sees this as a tower? Something about it simultaneously fascinates me and gives me vertigo.

user.name: biologist
text: You want this tower to only go six-feet-under? Jesus, @lonewolfsurveyor, talk about unsettling.

user.name: biologist
text: She didn't have to literally dig her grave with that remark. but whatever, she went first.

user.name: biologist
text: Alright world, cheers in case you don't hear from us again. No sunlight from here on.

user.name: biologist
text: We found some bizarre vines that are interlaced that make writing on the wall. Too dark to take pics.

user.name: biologist
text: Says "Where lies the strangling fruit that came from the hand of the sinner shall bring forth the seeds of the dead to share with the worms that…" and rambles on.

user.name: biologist
text: Something is wrong with those fruiting bodies. I directed @lonewolfsurveyor and @anthro_hiker to leave, we should be wearing masks.

user.name: biologist
text: Twitter, RT and lmk if I start acting really weird out of no where…

user.name: anthropologist
text: "Interesting"? That's it? That's all you got from seeing that wonderful structure? @psychminds343

user.name: biologist
text: As much as I appreciate observing the Area X biosphere, I feel like it's returning its gaze threateningly.

user.name: biologist
text: I'm now keeping too many secrets for me to feel comfortable with. Not sure if confessing would help or hurt @lonewoldsurveyor / @anthro_hiker…

user.name: biologist
text: We're heading to the tower, but if you want to talk @anthro_hiker, send me a message. Somethings up.

user.name: biologist
text: It's just me and @lonewolfsurveyor in the tower, and the tower's walls ARE LITERALLY BREATHING

user.name: biologist
text: Exploring this tower is renewing my old sense of discovery I had with nature as a child.

user.name: biologist
text: I remember back, my parents neglected a pool, and I  would watch the moss grow, algae, dragonflies, bullfrogs, turtles, etc became objects of my study

user.name: biologist
text: I missed being that connected.

user.name: biologist
text: This tower's throbbing has gotten unbearably loud. I know I sound crazy.

user.name: biologist
text: The writing on the wall is getting fresher. @lonewolfsurveyor and I are hastily descending to figure this out.

user.name: biologist
text: Trailing behind @lonewolfsurveyor as we investigate deeper into this tower. Something is making the writing appear…

user.name: biologist
text: We've made a horrifying discovery.

user.name: biologist
text: @lonewolfsurveyor believe me or don't, when we return to the surface we need an action plan for @psychminds343

user.name: biologist
text: Returning to the surface with more answers than questions. What happened to the anthropologist? Why is this tower unmapped?

user.name: biologist
text: Why was the base camp close to the tower and not the lighthouse? We've been hypnotized to not ask questions

user.name: biologist
text: I keep thinking back to my husband. He was on the eleventh expedition; I was alone for so long. Then he suddenly came home.

user.name: biologist
text: But he was never himself again. He was here, he wasn't here, and eventually he left this world forever. I demand answers from Area X

user.name: surveyor
text: this is bullshit. i dont know what to believe anymore. but we literally found her body, so im keeping the bio girl close

user.name: biologist
text: We're at a loss for words. Can't find the psychologist anywhere. At base camp now, feeling uneasy

user.name: biologist
text: Not seeing eye-to-eye on next steps. @lonewolfsurveyor wants to return home, I say there's still some work to be done.

user.name: biologist
text: Working on analyzing the samples that were collected, including the one from the anthologist's last moments.

user.name: biologist
text: The sample I collected of some of the roots by the tower flourished in this jar, creating their own ecosystem. Insane...

user.name: biologist
text: The anthropologist's sample was unexpected and seems of human brain tissue, or pretending? So many questions

user.name: biologist
text: @lonewolfsurveyor TOWER. We'll see…

user.name: biologist
text: Up for the night watch, there's an orange light coming from I think the lighthouse

user.name: biologist
text: My marriage had its highs and lows. We had a hard time seeing each other in the eye, our passions were so different.

user.name: biologist
text: We argued intensely when we left. When he came back, I didn't take a moment for granted, I took him in. I missed every second

user.name: biologist
text: The surveyor and I are not going to come to agreement on next steps. So I'll go where I believe nature is pointing me, even if alone.

user.name: surveyor
text: @bio_adventurer signed her own death warrant going up to the enemys high ground with a weapons cache. shes done

user.name: biologist
text: My quest to the lighthouse remains hopeful in search of truth

user.name: biologist
text: With the Crawler, the writing on the wall, and bizarre interaction I keep witnessing with the nature here, I hope for answers to reveal themselves

user.name: biologist
text: Is the writing on the call fertilization for the tower? This is maddening the more I think of it

user.name: biologist
text: I'm convinced one thing now. What we we're told of Area X is not the truth. I must find it myself.

user.name: biologist
text: I'm at a quaint, eerie, deserted village. Appears safe so far. Collecting samples as I go

user.name: biologist
text: Dolphins … with … human eyes. I can't shake this chill. It must have been an illusion.

user.name: biologist
text: Just crossed the defensive wall of the lighthouse, so one can shoot from the window. Going in now. Wish me luck Twitter

user.name: biologist
text: Entire wars have been fought by man inside the backroom of this lighthouse

user.name: biologist
text: Bullet holes and debris everywhere. Now it's just mold, dust, and quiet. Worse, in my opinion

user.name: biologist
text: A photograph of two fishermen was nailed to the wall. Possible lighthouse keeper? The circle around one of them arouses my interest

user.name: biologist
text: No one but dust and debris at the top.

user.name: biologist
text: Uncovered a trapdoor under a rug, large room with hundreds of journals and records of expeditions. Psychologist was here

user.name: biologist
text: Took me a decade, but I realize I've become that "old biologist" the people at Rock Bay would mock me for.

user.name: biologist
text: The world's madness is consuming me. "Ghost Bird" becomes clearer and clearer every day

user.name: biologist
text: Overwhelmed by clutter. Passionately motivated.

user.name: biologist
text: I can't bring myself to read it right now, but a piece of him was reunited with me

user.name: biologist
text: Left to get fresh air, I believe I found the psychologist on the ground level. Slowly going down to make sure it's not a trap.

user.name: biologist
text: She couldn't surrender her need to control the situation even in her final moments.

user.name: biologist
text: I'm not sure if I'll get all the answers to the questions I have now. She died keeping them reserved to herself.

user.name: biologist
text: Reading her notes, "Annihilation", the keyword that makes us all commit suicide under hypnosis. She can't push that button anymore.

user.name: biologist
text: I fought my husband before he left. He wanted something more fulfilling and challenging. I couldn't grasp that.

user.name: biologist
text: I never begged him to stay. I don't think I was able to grasp that. I don't blame him for leaving.

user.name: biologist
text: Should make it back to base camp by midnight. The thought of being near the psychologist's body makes me queasy

user.name: biologist
text: I'm being chased, but by nothing. These woods are making gutteral moaning sounds and I'm the target

user.name: biologist
text: Didn't mean to pass out last night. Almost at the base camp, rehearsing what I need to say to the surveyor.

user.name: biologist
text: Also, there's my hands are faintly glowing of phosphorescense. Whatever it is, I want this moaning to stop already

user.name: biologist
text: There weren't any peaceful negotiations. I fought for my life. You made your decision.

user.name: biologist
text: I've been ill since yesterday, but I'm recovered. Not sure how connected this is to the brightness, but the Tower keeps calling to me

user.name: biologist
text: It's time, I'm procrastinating this as much as we all deny this is happening

user.name: biologist
text: Pain. Comfort. I feel like I'm with him again. I wish I could have listened. I wish I was there when you needed Ghost Bird

user.name: biologist
text: We can't talk today but we'll see each other again, Captain

user.name: biologist
text: At the Tower, the heartbeat is stronger than before

user.name: biologist
text: I'm at the level where we found the anthropologist. The Tower's heartbeat is louder. No time to waste

user.name: biologist
text: Agony. I've passed the Crawler, who drowned me with a raging waterfall. Not sure if I survived that.

user.name: biologist
text: I think he recognizes me now, so I was able to get past him

user.name: biologist
text: I can't continue. Very close, but my body is stopping me. It's too painful

user.name: biologist
text: The illuminating Crawler was the fisherman from the photo. How long he's been here, or how I can help, is beyond me

user.name: biologist
text: I believe the Crawler works in cycles, and when he reaches the end, Area X enters a convulsive season of barricades and blood

user.name: biologist
text: His fate is settled, and the souls of every other expeditioners exists on Area X in some other natural form

user.name: biologist
text: I will continue on my journey for answers. From here on I'm logging out. I am not returning home.
